Subject: [PATCH] patch 0888: cache key includes company hint + hardcoded NSE
 ticker-name map

The real reason 0887 was not visibly helping: /api/v1/news-india/<ticker>
KV cache returned a STALE ticker-only payload before applying the new
company hint. So even though the home page started passing
company=Bliss%20GVS for BLISSGVS, the route handler hit the cache, saw
a yesterday-fetched ticker-only result, and short-circuited - the
company hint never reached fetchIndianNews.

Two fixes:

1. /api/v1/news-india KEY() now includes the company suffix, and the
   version bumps to v2 so old ticker-only entries do not poison the new
   namespace. KV reads + writes both use the company-aware key.

2. New file lib/nse-ticker-names.ts with NSE_TICKER_NAMES - a hardcoded
   map of ~110 common Indian smallcap/midcap tickers to their long-form
   names (BLISSGVS -> "Bliss GVS Pharma", MARKSANS -> "Marksans Pharma",
   ASTRAMICRO -> "Astra Microwave Products", ANUPAMRAS -> "Anupam
   Rasayan" etc).

3. Home page imports this map and merges it into companyNameByTicker
   FIRST, so it acts as the authoritative source. User localStorage
   uploads layer on top to fill gaps; heuristic split is the final
   fallback. Result: for any of the ~110 hardcoded names, news search
   passes the real company name to /api/v1/news AND
   /api/v1/news-india, RSS feeds match, classifier catches it.

For BLISSGVS specifically on next deploy:
  - companyNameByTicker[BLISSGVS] = "Bliss GVS Pharma" (from hardcoded map)
  - mainSearch query becomes "Bliss GVS Pharma BLISSGVS"
  - /api/v1/news-india/BLISSGVS?company=Bliss%20GVS%20Pharma
  - Cache key becomes news-india:v2:BLISSGVS::bliss-gvs-pharma (fresh,
    no stale ticker-only entry)
  - fetchIndianNews uses "Bliss GVS Pharma" as Google News query and
    in Moneycontrol/Business Standard post-filter token set
  - One of Google News, Moneycontrol, or BS returns the acquisition
    article ("Bliss GVS hits 20% upper circuit as Anupam Rasayan to
    acquire 43% stake for Rs 1,369 crore")
  - 0882 ACQUISITION pattern matches "acquir(?:es|ed|ing).{0,80}?43%
    stake" -> chip becomes "acquires 43% stake in Bliss GVS Pharma"
